<doc id="351177" wikidata="Q480817" url="?curid=351177" title="Cutlassfish">
<text>The cutlassfishes are about 45 species of predatory ray-finned fish in the family Trichiuridae of the order Scombriformes found in seas throughout the world. Fish of this family are long, slender, and generally steely blue or silver in colour, giving rise to their name. They have reduced or absent pelvic and caudal fins, giving them an eel-like appearance, and large fang-like teeth.

Some of the species are known as scabbardfishes or hairtails; others are called frostfishes because they appear in late autumn and early winter, around the time of the first frosts.

==Classification==
This list of species follows FishBase:

* Subfamily Aphanopidinae 
** †Genus &quot;Anenchelum&quot; (Early Eocene to Late Miocene)
** Genus &quot;Aphanopus&quot;
*** &quot;Aphanopus arigato&quot; 
*** &quot;Aphanopus beckeri&quot; 
*** &quot;Aphanopus capricornis&quot; 
*** &quot;Aphanopus carbo&quot; (Black scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Aphanopus intermedius&quot; (Intermediate scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Aphanopus microphthalmus&quot; (Smalleye scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Aphanopus mikhailini&quot; (Mikhailin&#x27;s scabbardfish)
** Genus &quot;Benthodesmus&quot; 
*** &quot;Benthodesmus elongatus&quot;, (Elongate frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus macrophthalmus&quot;, (Bigeye frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus neglectus&quot;, (Neglected frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus oligoradiatus&quot;, (Sparse-rayed frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus pacificus&quot;, (North Pacific frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus papua&quot;, (Papuan frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus simonyi&quot;, (Simony&#x27;s frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus suluensis&quot;, (Philippine frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus tenuis&quot;, (Slender frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus tuckeri&quot;, (Tucker&#x27;s frostfish)
*** &quot;Benthodesmus vityazi&quot;, (Vityaz&#x27; frostfish)
* Subfamily Lepidopodinae, 
** Genus &quot;Assurger&quot;
*** &quot;Assurger anzac&quot; (Razorback scabbardfish)
** Genus &quot;Eupleurogrammus&quot;
*** &quot;Eupleurogrammus glossodon&quot;, (Longtooth hairtail)
*** &quot;Eupleurogrammus muticus&quot;, (Smallhead hairtail)
** Genus &quot;Evoxymetopon&quot;
*** &quot;Evoxymetopon macrophthalmus&quot; 
*** &quot;Evoxymetopon moricheni&quot; 
*** &quot;Evoxymetopon poeyi&quot; (Poey&#x27;s scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Evoxymetopon taeniatus&quot; (Channel scabbardfish)
** Genus &quot;Lepidopus&quot;
*** &quot;Lepidopus altifrons&quot;, (Crested scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Lepidopus calcar&quot;, (Hawaiian ridge scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Lepidopus caudatus&quot;, (Silver scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Lepidopus dubius&quot;, (Doubtful scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Lepidopus fitchi &quot;, (Fitch&#x27;s scabbardfish)
*** &quot;Lepidopus manis&quot;, (Ghost scabbardfish)
*Subfamily Trichiurinae 
** Genus &quot;Demissolinea&quot;
*** &quot;Demissolinea novaeguineensis&quot;, (New Guinean hairtail)
**Genus †&quot;Eutrichiurides&quot; (Eocene to Oligocene)
** Genus &quot;Lepturacanthus&quot;
*** &quot;Lepturacanthus pantului&quot;, (Coromandel hairtail)
*** &quot;Lepturacanthus roelandti&quot; 
*** &quot;Lepturacanthus savala&quot;, (Savalani hairtail)
** Genus &quot;Tentoriceps&quot;
*** &quot;Tentoriceps cristatus&quot;, (Crested hairtail)
**Genus †&quot;Trichiurides&quot; (Eocene)
** Genus &quot;Trichiurus&quot;
*** &quot;Trichiurus auriga&quot;, (Pearly hairtail)
*** &quot;Trichiurus australis&quot; 
*** &quot;Trichiurus brevis&quot;, (Chinese short-tailed hairtail)
*** &quot;Trichiurus gangeticus&quot;, (Ganges hairtail)
*** &quot;Trichiurus lepturus&quot;, (Largehead hairtail)
*** &quot;Trichiurus margarites&quot;, 
*** &quot;Trichiurus nanhaiensis&quot;, 
*** &quot;Trichiurus nickolensis&quot;, (Australian short-tailed hairtail)
*** &quot;Trichiurus russelli&quot;, (Short-tailed hairtail)

